WEBVTT

00:00:01.731 --> 00:00:03.858
Stimulants, narcotics, cannabis.

00:00:05.110 --> 00:00:07.237
People who have used these drugs

00:00:07.320 --> 00:00:10.824
are now estimated
to total two million in Japan.

00:00:11.366 --> 00:00:14.452
The number of people arrested
for drug-related offenses

00:00:15.036 --> 00:00:17.163
is as many as 14,000 yearly.

00:00:18.289 --> 00:00:22.502
I won't tell a soul
that I bought from the Saeki Family!

00:00:22.585 --> 00:00:24.796
Please, have mercy on me!

00:00:28.508 --> 00:00:32.303
This adds damage to property
on top of inflicting bodily injury.

00:00:32.387 --> 00:00:33.304
Come on, man!

00:00:33.388 --> 00:00:36.266
Cutting my face? Have you gone insane?

00:00:36.349 --> 00:00:38.226
Are you fucking mad?

00:00:38.309 --> 00:00:42.063
The NCD has Kurosaki, who'll use
any means to make a suspect talk.

00:00:42.146 --> 00:00:45.441
His mother
wasn't just a regular meth addict.

00:00:46.609 --> 00:00:50.655
She was fed meth and forced
into becoming a sex addict.

00:00:51.656 --> 00:00:53.241
It's your fault.

00:00:53.324 --> 00:00:55.118
Meth laid waste to his family.

00:00:55.743 --> 00:00:59.038
That's why he bears
a deep hatred for drugs.

00:00:59.122 --> 00:01:00.874
To avenge his mother.

00:01:00.957 --> 00:01:03.585
So he's not just an asshole.

00:01:04.878 --> 00:01:06.045
What is this?

00:01:06.129 --> 00:01:07.338
Hey, wait!

00:01:07.422 --> 00:01:09.215
What are you doing?

00:01:09.299 --> 00:01:10.842
Isn't she a victim?

00:01:12.260 --> 00:01:14.387
-Let's go.
-Wait!

00:01:14.888 --> 00:01:19.726
I said you would hurt those dear to you
and lose everything if you did drugs.

00:01:20.476 --> 00:01:23.354
Please, just come back
to your senses, you idiot!

00:01:35.992 --> 00:01:39.704
The urine test detected
cocaine metabolites.

00:01:41.831 --> 00:01:43.041
You tested positive.

00:01:52.759 --> 00:01:55.345
What is your relationship
with Hibiki Kaga?

00:01:57.931 --> 00:02:02.477
Kaga forced you into taking cocaine,
and then you couldn't stop.

00:02:03.603 --> 00:02:04.687
Isn't that so?

00:02:09.817 --> 00:02:11.819
Start talking and answer me.

00:02:20.578 --> 00:02:23.331
She was cooperative with the urine test.

00:02:24.374 --> 00:02:26.668
She has to be hiding something.

00:02:27.418 --> 00:02:29.879
Maybe she likes Kaga
and is covering for him.

00:02:29.963 --> 00:02:33.091
No, that's not the impression I get.

00:02:33.633 --> 00:02:35.301
But there's still something.

00:02:37.595 --> 00:02:38.596
Chief.

00:02:39.514 --> 00:02:41.474
Let me conduct the questioning.

00:02:42.684 --> 00:02:45.812
You know he won't let
anyone else take charge of it.

00:02:46.521 --> 00:02:49.148
There are things women
can only tell other women.

00:02:50.066 --> 00:02:53.361
Especially if a man put her
through a terrible experience.

00:02:55.780 --> 00:03:00.702
She may be a drug user,
but she could also be a victim.

00:03:01.285 --> 00:03:02.412
Please.

00:03:03.830 --> 00:03:09.085
For her, this interrogation could define
her whole life going forward.

00:03:14.757 --> 00:03:16.759
Go convince Kurosaki.

00:03:18.344 --> 00:03:19.220
Yes, sir.

00:03:24.058 --> 00:03:25.393
You sure about that?

00:03:26.352 --> 00:03:27.478
Yes.

00:03:29.856 --> 00:03:32.358
You two could learn
a thing or two from her.

00:04:27.872 --> 00:04:29.665
This room is occupied.

00:04:29.749 --> 00:04:31.209
Give me just ten minutes.

00:04:31.292 --> 00:04:33.461
-No. Get out.
-Please!

00:04:34.670 --> 00:04:36.672
What can a rookie
like you even accomplish?

00:04:42.595 --> 00:04:43.429
Are those…

00:05:08.955 --> 00:05:10.498
Hesitation marks?

00:05:17.630 --> 00:05:19.215
I was scared…

00:05:21.342 --> 00:05:22.468
of dying.

00:05:35.106 --> 00:05:36.232
I'm glad.

00:05:38.192 --> 00:05:39.485
What?

00:05:42.238 --> 00:05:44.448
That you weren't bold enough to die.

00:05:52.248 --> 00:05:53.416
I'm sorry.

00:05:55.042 --> 00:05:57.753
If only we had caught Kaga sooner,

00:05:58.421 --> 00:06:01.048
you wouldn't have had to go through this.

00:06:09.807 --> 00:06:11.225
Just five minutes.

00:06:11.767 --> 00:06:14.061
Let me ask what she's going through.

00:06:39.337 --> 00:06:41.547
You're saying you did cocaine,

00:06:42.465 --> 00:06:44.425
so you could forget about Kaga?

00:06:46.928 --> 00:06:48.012
Yes.

00:06:51.057 --> 00:06:52.266
Over and over,

00:06:55.353 --> 00:06:58.856
I would see his face.

00:07:01.192 --> 00:07:03.402
It wouldn't leave my mind.

00:07:05.238 --> 00:07:06.280
Flashbacks.

00:07:08.866 --> 00:07:12.703
Was this the first time you bought
and did cocaine by yourself?

00:07:17.291 --> 00:07:18.751
It was my second time.

00:07:22.296 --> 00:07:24.632
When I did it by myself the first time,

00:07:26.342 --> 00:07:31.389
I was able to forget about him,
even for just a moment.

00:07:32.682 --> 00:07:33.724
I see.

00:07:34.892 --> 00:07:36.435
It must have been tough.

00:07:39.480 --> 00:07:40.648
But you know,

00:07:41.774 --> 00:07:44.360
even if you use drugs
when times are tough,

00:07:45.152 --> 00:07:48.531
it gets worse when the drugs run out,
and you get withdrawal.

00:07:49.448 --> 00:07:51.409
Then you turn to drugs again.

00:07:53.327 --> 00:07:56.747
It makes you unable
to keep on living without cocaine.

00:08:01.377 --> 00:08:02.420
Listen.

00:08:03.921 --> 00:08:07.967
Don't throw away the rest of your life
because of a horrible man like him.

00:08:11.554 --> 00:08:14.223
We'll make sure Kaga
pays for what he has done.

00:08:15.433 --> 00:08:19.186
We'll do whatever we can
to alleviate your worries.

00:08:19.270 --> 00:08:20.896
I promise you!

00:08:31.032 --> 00:08:33.117
Thank you.

00:08:48.716 --> 00:08:50.468
There.

00:08:57.183 --> 00:08:59.477
She's a victim! So why--

00:08:59.560 --> 00:09:01.604
She's no longer a victim
if she buys cocaine herself!

00:09:02.772 --> 00:09:05.149
We have a responsibility to arrest her.

00:09:05.983 --> 00:09:07.652
You're a dealer.

00:09:07.735 --> 00:09:10.655
You should already know
the hell that awaits her.

00:09:19.622 --> 00:09:21.832
What's wrong? Not going to eat that?

00:09:21.916 --> 00:09:25.753
I mean, anyone would get tired
of okonomiyaki two days in a row.

00:09:28.047 --> 00:09:28.881
Yum!

00:09:30.174 --> 00:09:33.344
Yesterday's were Hiroshima style.
These are Kure City style.

00:09:33.427 --> 00:09:36.764
The half-moon look is
the main difference between them.

00:09:36.847 --> 00:09:39.433
It uses Kure's specialty
thin udon noodles.

00:09:40.226 --> 00:09:42.061
Listen, there are several varieties

00:09:42.144 --> 00:09:45.106
under the umbrella
of Hiroshima's okonomiyaki.

00:09:45.189 --> 00:09:48.734
The taste and texture differ
based on the use of soba or udon.

00:09:48.818 --> 00:09:51.529
That is what defines
Hiroshima's okonomiyaki.

00:09:54.699 --> 00:09:57.034
I don't care as long as it tastes good.

00:09:57.118 --> 00:09:58.661
But come on,

00:09:58.744 --> 00:10:02.415
you didn't call me just to lecture me
on Hiroshima's okonomiyaki.

00:10:07.420 --> 00:10:11.549
We found out that Nagata's company
is linked to the Saeki Family.

00:10:11.632 --> 00:10:14.885
Nagata is the guy
who sold drugs to Kaga, right?

00:10:15.594 --> 00:10:17.388
He's linked to the yakuza too?

00:10:17.471 --> 00:10:20.599
Matsubara, your boss,
also gets cocaine from the Saeki Family.

00:10:20.683 --> 00:10:21.767
You didn't know that?

00:10:21.851 --> 00:10:24.895
No, us underlings weren't told
any details about the route.

00:10:26.605 --> 00:10:30.234
That's most likely how
Nagata got his cocaine.

00:10:30.317 --> 00:10:31.444
Given that,

00:10:32.361 --> 00:10:36.532
your job is to make Kurosaki accept
a plan prepared by the police.

00:10:36.615 --> 00:10:37.908
What?

00:10:37.992 --> 00:10:40.202
You know Kurosaki won't listen to me.

00:10:40.286 --> 00:10:42.663
This is what you'll suggest to Kurosaki,

00:10:43.330 --> 00:10:44.665
"Let's get not just Nagata,

00:10:44.749 --> 00:10:48.002
but also the organization
that was selling drugs to him.

00:10:48.085 --> 00:10:50.629
I'll go and investigate
their smuggling routes."

00:10:50.713 --> 00:10:53.257
You think Kurosaki would fall for that?

00:10:53.340 --> 00:10:57.094
If you share the information that Nagata
got his cocaine from the Saeki Family,

00:10:57.178 --> 00:10:59.096
Kurosaki will definitely bite.

00:10:59.847 --> 00:11:03.100
Why would you let Kurosaki
know that anyway?

00:11:03.184 --> 00:11:05.728
Isn't the NCD
a rival organization to the police?

00:11:05.811 --> 00:11:08.397
Why not just conduct
your own investigation?

00:11:08.481 --> 00:11:10.941
As a trade-off for
the police's great authority,

00:11:11.025 --> 00:11:15.362
the law binds us tightly and oversees us,
so we can't do aggressive investigations.

00:11:16.071 --> 00:11:18.782
On the other hand,
the NCD has special privileges,

00:11:18.866 --> 00:11:21.035
such as the right to do sting operations.

00:11:21.118 --> 00:11:24.455
That's why we let them gather evidence,

00:11:24.538 --> 00:11:28.501
and you'll leak it to us by sticking
to Kurosaki as an S for the NCD.

00:11:30.127 --> 00:11:34.757
So you'll let the NCD do all the work,
then swoop in to steal the credit?

00:11:34.840 --> 00:11:35.799
Not quite.

00:11:35.883 --> 00:11:38.177
We'll utilize the NCD
to the fullest extent,

00:11:38.260 --> 00:11:39.803
and arrest the culprits at the end.

00:11:39.887 --> 00:11:41.305
Same difference.

00:11:41.388 --> 00:11:44.767
In other words,
fatten the pigs before you slaughter them.

00:11:46.644 --> 00:11:48.521
Should a cop be saying that?

00:11:48.604 --> 00:11:49.522
Right.

00:11:51.190 --> 00:11:52.274
One more thing.

00:11:52.358 --> 00:11:53.359
What?

00:11:56.487 --> 00:11:57.655
What are these?

00:11:57.738 --> 00:11:59.907
I want you to infiltrate the Saeki Family.

00:12:00.574 --> 00:12:01.450
What?!

00:12:01.534 --> 00:12:03.619
Get your hands on their goods
and collect evidence.

00:12:03.702 --> 00:12:05.538
No, why me?

00:12:05.621 --> 00:12:08.749
Infiltrate the yakuza?
Hell no. That's crazy dangerous.

00:12:08.832 --> 00:12:10.084
You don't get to refuse.

00:12:10.167 --> 00:12:11.460
First off,

00:12:11.544 --> 00:12:15.464
they wouldn't let a nobody like me
have access to their precious merchandise.

00:12:16.674 --> 00:12:18.175
Don't you worry.

00:12:18.259 --> 00:12:21.053
The police will apply
some pressure to help you out.

00:12:46.537 --> 00:12:48.581
What the hell? Who?

00:12:53.043 --> 00:12:54.628
Long time no see.

00:13:01.343 --> 00:13:03.345
You little shit.

00:13:04.513 --> 00:13:06.515
You can't meet your damn quota.

00:13:09.268 --> 00:13:11.687
You don't bother to keep in touch.

00:13:13.147 --> 00:13:17.192
I may be the merciful kind,
but even I have a fucking limit!

00:13:22.531 --> 00:13:24.325
Sorry, I had some things to deal with.

00:13:24.408 --> 00:13:27.286
I don't give a flying fuck
about your circumstances!

00:13:27.369 --> 00:13:28.412
I'll kill your ass.

00:13:30.664 --> 00:13:31.540
I'm sorry.

00:13:32.333 --> 00:13:33.584
I'll get the money.

00:13:34.168 --> 00:13:37.212
Then prepare ten million,
interest included.

00:13:37.296 --> 00:13:40.591
-Ten million?
-Damn right. You're way past the deadline.

00:13:40.674 --> 00:13:41.925
But ten million is just--

00:13:42.009 --> 00:13:43.218
Too much?

00:13:43.302 --> 00:13:44.887
Then here's an idea.

00:13:48.974 --> 00:13:50.684
How about we go for an eyeball?

00:13:50.768 --> 00:13:52.436
Please wait!

00:13:52.519 --> 00:13:54.730
You can get 500k for each one.

00:13:54.813 --> 00:13:56.940
I'll prepare the money ASAP.

00:13:58.400 --> 00:14:01.153
You think I'm going to trust that?

00:14:02.613 --> 00:14:03.447
Don't!

00:14:06.742 --> 00:14:07.618
Wait.

00:14:08.202 --> 00:14:09.203
What?

00:14:10.579 --> 00:14:12.164
That's right.

00:14:12.247 --> 00:14:13.749
I almost forgot.

00:14:15.084 --> 00:14:16.210
Sorry?

00:14:16.293 --> 00:14:20.589
The Saeki Family that has been looking
after us needs some more manpower.

00:14:22.132 --> 00:14:23.050
You.

00:14:23.592 --> 00:14:25.135
Go help them for a few days.

00:14:25.219 --> 00:14:27.179
What? Why me?

00:14:27.262 --> 00:14:30.474
Fuck if I know! It's orders from above!

00:14:31.308 --> 00:14:33.477
Or would you rather offer the eyeballs?

00:14:34.019 --> 00:14:35.104
I'll go.

00:14:35.646 --> 00:14:36.855
Seriously…

00:14:37.856 --> 00:14:40.818
We got ordered to give up
our meth rights unilaterally,

00:14:40.901 --> 00:14:42.778
which is a real fucking bummer.

00:14:42.861 --> 00:14:44.071
Don't you worry.

00:14:44.613 --> 00:14:47.408
The police will apply
some pressure to help you out.

00:14:48.826 --> 00:14:50.869
They don't seem to like it either.

00:14:52.204 --> 00:14:54.123
Who's gaining anything from it?

00:15:05.426 --> 00:15:07.094
Mr. Matsubara sent me.

00:15:07.177 --> 00:15:08.470
I'm Umezawa.

00:15:08.554 --> 00:15:09.555
Nice to meet you.

00:15:16.061 --> 00:15:17.688
Wipe your soles with this.

00:15:17.771 --> 00:15:18.689
What?

00:15:19.189 --> 00:15:20.065
Yes, sir.

00:15:21.316 --> 00:15:22.860
I hear you're a dealer?

00:15:22.943 --> 00:15:23.944
Yes, sir.

00:15:24.028 --> 00:15:25.738
Give us your client list.

00:15:25.821 --> 00:15:28.240
-What?
-A list of your online customers!

00:15:28.824 --> 00:15:30.242
-Yes, sir.
-Hurry it up.

00:15:30.868 --> 00:15:32.494
Let's see. Here it is.

00:15:35.914 --> 00:15:37.082
What?

00:15:37.166 --> 00:15:38.584
Only 60 people?

00:15:40.002 --> 00:15:42.421
Yes, I mostly sold in person.

00:15:44.506 --> 00:15:45.591
I guess it'll do.

00:15:46.175 --> 00:15:48.427
Refer those customers to us from now on.

00:15:49.845 --> 00:15:51.388
What? But that's…

00:15:52.097 --> 00:15:53.599
Got a problem with that?

00:15:56.685 --> 00:15:57.644
None.

00:15:58.353 --> 00:16:00.689
So, what will I be doing?

00:16:02.149 --> 00:16:03.984
Think about that yourself.

00:16:04.610 --> 00:16:05.444
Hello, sir.

00:16:05.527 --> 00:16:06.695
Hello, sir.

00:16:09.573 --> 00:16:12.534
If you can't think for yourself,
stick to wiping the floors.

00:16:13.410 --> 00:16:14.286
Wiping the floors?

00:16:14.912 --> 00:16:16.163
What? You don't like it?

00:16:16.747 --> 00:16:17.664
No, sir.

00:16:18.707 --> 00:16:19.750
Listen up.

00:16:19.833 --> 00:16:23.170
One look at how they clean
and I can tell if they're useful.

00:16:23.253 --> 00:16:25.839
If they seem trustworthy,
they'll get the goods.

00:16:25.923 --> 00:16:27.966
Shouldn't be a bad deal.

00:16:28.050 --> 00:16:28.884
Yes, sir.

00:16:32.012 --> 00:16:34.306
Hey. Who wiped the table today?

00:16:35.099 --> 00:16:37.267
Sorry, I was still in the middle of it.

00:16:37.351 --> 00:16:38.852
No excuses!

00:16:39.353 --> 00:16:40.687
I'm sorry, sir.

00:16:43.816 --> 00:16:45.484
Hey. What's this?

00:16:45.567 --> 00:16:47.027
Sir, that was me.

00:16:47.111 --> 00:16:48.612
You got fingerprints on it!

00:16:49.822 --> 00:16:50.697
Sorry, sir.

00:16:50.781 --> 00:16:51.740
Hey.

00:16:52.950 --> 00:16:53.909
Like I always say,

00:16:54.827 --> 00:16:56.537
a dirty room equals a careless mind.

00:16:56.620 --> 00:16:58.080
Every little bit adds up.

00:16:58.664 --> 00:17:00.249
A small error could prove fatal.

00:17:00.332 --> 00:17:01.834
Do it properly.

00:17:01.917 --> 00:17:02.960
Right, Shinichi?

00:17:03.544 --> 00:17:04.419
I'm Shinji, sir.

00:17:04.503 --> 00:17:06.505
Does it fucking matter?

00:17:07.256 --> 00:17:09.633
-I'm Shinichi--
-You too!

00:17:13.887 --> 00:17:16.348
The guy is an actual psycho.

00:17:16.431 --> 00:17:18.684
A clean freak yakuza? Give me a break.

00:17:19.852 --> 00:17:21.311
It's not a joke!

00:17:21.395 --> 00:17:24.106
Well, at least the infiltration went well.

00:17:25.232 --> 00:17:27.568
All thanks to the pressure
you guys applied.

00:17:27.651 --> 00:17:30.988
They've got their backers too.
The higher-ups are all connected.

00:17:31.613 --> 00:17:33.782
Police, yakuza. Is there a difference?

00:17:33.866 --> 00:17:37.578
Next, you have to make Kurosaki
accept this plan.

00:17:38.078 --> 00:17:41.331
Crushing a trafficking operation
should be tempting to him.

00:17:41.415 --> 00:17:43.584
Right, I still have to do that.

00:17:43.667 --> 00:17:47.546
Just so we're clear,
if Kurosaki catches on to this plan,

00:17:48.088 --> 00:17:49.965
you will stop being an S for the NCD

00:17:50.048 --> 00:17:52.926
and become a roach
harmful to their investigation.

00:17:53.760 --> 00:17:56.263
That is to say,
a traitor to be disposed of.

00:17:56.346 --> 00:17:58.932
By dispose, you mean they'll arrest me?

00:17:59.016 --> 00:18:01.560
Would be nice if that's all it was.

00:18:01.643 --> 00:18:03.687
Wait, you'll help if it gets bad, right?

00:18:03.770 --> 00:18:06.231
You will also lose value
as an S for the police.

00:18:06.315 --> 00:18:08.066
You'll have to wipe your own ass.

00:18:08.150 --> 00:18:09.276
You can't be serious!

00:18:09.359 --> 00:18:11.069
To avoid that,

00:18:11.820 --> 00:18:14.907
take the utmost care
not to let Kurosaki catch on to us.

00:18:15.866 --> 00:18:20.495
His instinct on drug-related matters
is monstrously accurate, after all.

00:18:22.497 --> 00:18:23.874
Damn.

00:18:44.394 --> 00:18:46.855
Can you not brew coffee in my house?

00:18:48.732 --> 00:18:51.276
What did you want to discuss? Get to it.

00:18:53.737 --> 00:18:54.905
Yes, well,

00:18:55.530 --> 00:18:58.242
you remember the talk
about adding a new cocaine route

00:18:58.325 --> 00:19:00.410
to people connected to Nagata?

00:19:00.494 --> 00:19:01.662
Yes.

00:19:01.745 --> 00:19:03.205
How about we don't do that?

00:19:03.956 --> 00:19:06.375
What? Insubordination? I'll arrest you.

00:19:06.458 --> 00:19:07.960
Come on, just listen.

00:19:08.585 --> 00:19:12.381
If we follow your plan,
it puts me in a really bad position.

00:19:12.464 --> 00:19:15.842
I could die if the traffickers
set their sights on me.

00:19:15.926 --> 00:19:17.761
Endeavor not to die. Request denied.

00:19:17.844 --> 00:19:18.887
Let me finish.

00:19:18.971 --> 00:19:20.055
Go on.

00:19:21.890 --> 00:19:22.933
Right.

00:19:24.017 --> 00:19:27.271
Catching the guys selling to Nagata
would be nice and all,

00:19:27.354 --> 00:19:31.650
but wouldn't it be even better to catch
the underlying organization behind it all?

00:19:31.733 --> 00:19:34.695
And how would we investigate
the said organization?

00:19:34.778 --> 00:19:37.364
The NCD is still working
to pin them down right now.

00:19:45.080 --> 00:19:46.331
The Saeki Family.

00:19:47.624 --> 00:19:50.544
Why would an underling like you know that?

00:19:51.378 --> 00:19:53.171
Even as an underling,

00:19:53.255 --> 00:19:56.091
once I knew that it was Nagata
giving Kaga cocaine,

00:19:56.633 --> 00:19:58.760
I had enough intel to piece it together.

00:20:00.429 --> 00:20:03.098
-Is that intel reliable?
-I promise you, it is.

00:20:04.224 --> 00:20:06.268
I already started tracking their trail.

00:20:10.230 --> 00:20:12.858
Unusually efficient and proactive of you.

00:20:13.358 --> 00:20:14.651
Is there a catch?

00:20:17.529 --> 00:20:20.741
I just want to raise my chances
of survival any way I can.

00:20:22.868 --> 00:20:25.954
We've had the Saeki Family
marked for some time now,

00:20:26.038 --> 00:20:27.873
but never had conclusive evidence.

00:20:29.166 --> 00:20:31.376
The NCD can do sting operations, right?

00:20:31.460 --> 00:20:35.172
In that case,
I'll infiltrate the smuggling operation.

00:20:36.757 --> 00:20:37.591
What?

00:20:37.674 --> 00:20:38.800
In other words,

00:20:41.428 --> 00:20:43.555
we fatten the pigs for the slaughter.

00:20:46.266 --> 00:20:47.642
Think about it.

00:20:48.268 --> 00:20:51.813
If I infiltrate it, we can grasp
the entire flow of the cocaine.

00:20:52.647 --> 00:20:53.690
With this plan,

00:20:53.774 --> 00:20:58.320
we can get more than just the people
who directly sold the cocaine to Nagata.

00:21:00.197 --> 00:21:02.783
I don't know what you're scheming…

00:21:04.576 --> 00:21:06.870
but I'm intrigued. I'm in.

00:21:06.953 --> 00:21:08.538
Okay, then let's be quick--

00:21:08.622 --> 00:21:09.623
That said,

00:21:09.706 --> 00:21:13.126
if you're infiltrating, you need
to bring back some evidence.

00:21:13.210 --> 00:21:14.336
Evidence?

00:21:14.419 --> 00:21:15.295
Yes.

00:21:15.962 --> 00:21:19.091
Information about big deals
or their smuggling routes.

00:21:19.174 --> 00:21:20.425
The client list.

00:21:20.926 --> 00:21:22.469
Where would I…

00:21:23.095 --> 00:21:25.847
Search for it. Find it. Bring it.
That's my condition.

00:21:28.141 --> 00:21:29.476
All right.

00:21:32.104 --> 00:21:32.938
Umezawa.

00:21:33.021 --> 00:21:33.980
What?

00:21:35.649 --> 00:21:36.483
Take this.

00:21:37.734 --> 00:21:39.277
What's this, all of a sudden?

00:21:39.361 --> 00:21:40.570
A good luck charm.

00:21:41.238 --> 00:21:43.532
What gives? You're creeping me out.

00:21:44.366 --> 00:21:46.701
You'll have to protect yourself.

00:21:46.785 --> 00:21:48.787
You weren't trying to be nice?

00:21:50.122 --> 00:21:51.081
Wait.

00:21:52.249 --> 00:21:53.708
Your legs fall asleep?

00:21:53.792 --> 00:21:55.043
No, they did not.

00:21:57.379 --> 00:21:58.296
There.

00:21:59.089 --> 00:22:00.048
Take that.

00:22:01.758 --> 00:22:03.677
-Here.
-Stop. I'll arrest you.

00:22:03.760 --> 00:22:07.055
Try it. Come on. Come at me.

00:22:07.681 --> 00:22:09.808
Just try it. Come on.

00:22:09.891 --> 00:22:12.853
Over here. Try and get me.

00:22:27.826 --> 00:22:29.077
Hello, sir!

00:22:29.786 --> 00:22:31.288
Where's Shinichi and Shinji?

00:22:31.371 --> 00:22:32.914
They went to buy drinks.

00:22:32.998 --> 00:22:34.916
They left a newbie alone?

00:22:45.051 --> 00:22:46.553
Did you wipe all of this?

00:22:46.636 --> 00:22:48.597
Sorry, it was me.

00:22:51.433 --> 00:22:52.559
You pass.

00:22:53.643 --> 00:22:54.519
What?

00:22:54.603 --> 00:22:56.730
Nice and thorough work.

00:22:57.772 --> 00:22:59.232
Thank you, sir.

00:22:59.316 --> 00:23:01.026
All right then.

00:23:01.109 --> 00:23:04.321
Go to the dock right now
and collect our monthly shipment.

00:23:05.405 --> 00:23:06.740
What kind of shipment?

00:23:08.658 --> 00:23:09.910
Cocaine.

00:23:11.661 --> 00:23:13.788
Someone else will handle the payment.

00:23:13.872 --> 00:23:16.833
You just get the shipment
and contact me immediately.

00:23:16.917 --> 00:23:18.335
Ask Shinichi the details.

00:23:18.919 --> 00:23:19.920
Yes, sir.

00:23:25.634 --> 00:23:27.093
That's mission accomplished.

00:23:27.677 --> 00:23:28.845
Great job.

00:23:28.929 --> 00:23:30.847
Want to try dying once?

00:23:30.931 --> 00:23:32.057
Who the hell are you?

00:23:32.641 --> 00:23:33.725
Hey!

00:23:33.808 --> 00:23:35.852
KUROSAKI RUSHES IN TO SAVE UMEZAWA?

00:23:35.936 --> 00:23:37.229
Don't move!

00:23:37.312 --> 00:23:38.188
Or he dies.

00:23:38.271 --> 00:23:40.565
But killing a narcotics agent…

00:23:40.649 --> 00:23:42.234
What other choice is there?

00:23:43.735 --> 00:23:45.028
How many will die?

00:23:45.111 --> 00:23:48.490
If their numbers are in both
of your phones, I'll trust you.

00:23:48.573 --> 00:23:49.699
However,

00:23:49.783 --> 00:23:51.993
if they aren't…

00:23:52.994 --> 00:23:54.496
it's over for you.

00:23:55.121 --> 00:24:01.044
ANY RESEMBLANCE TO ACTUAL PERSONS,
GROUPS, OR CASES IS PURELY COINCIDENTAL

00:24:01.127 --> 00:24:02.087
Subtitle translation by: Saim Ul Hassan